        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When i use Zend_Date to add 1 day and subtract 2 days for obtain next and previous day, it return wrong year.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n$date = new Zend_Date('2009-12-31');\r\n\r\n$date->add(1, Zend_Date::DAY); \/\/Expected 2010-01-01\r\n\r\necho $date; \/\/Return 2010-01-01 00:00:00, its all right\r\necho $date->get('Y'); \/\/Return 2009, wrong year!\r\necho $date->get(Zend_Date::YEAR); \/\/Return 2010, right!\r\n\r\n$date->sub(2, Zend_Date::DAY); \/\/Expected 2009-12-30\r\n\r\necho $date; \/\/Return 2009-12-30 00:00:00, its all right\r\necho $date->get('Y'); \/\/Return 2009, right!\r\necho $date->get(Zend_Date::YEAR); \/\/Return 2009, right!"
        },
